&lt;p&gt;Summary&lt;br/&gt;
-------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch is for capping the number of regions on a region server depending on different use-cases. We add a parameter in the config file which can be used by the user to set this value. The default value is INT_MAX. &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This addresses bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2844&quot; title=&quot;Capping the number of regions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2844&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2844&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
